==English==

==== Etymology ====
[[un-]] + [[equivocal]]

=== Adjective ===
'''unequivocal'''
# something which is [[said]] or [[spoken]] to be without [[equal]], [[matchless]]
#:''I wanted to do something in my life that was '''unequivocal'''.''
# without [[equivocation]] or [[ambiguity]]; singularly [[clear]], [[unmistakable]], or [[unquestionable]]
#:''At the time of its construction, the scope and size of the Golden Gate Bridge's construction was '''unequivocal'''.''

